ce:section.ce:para:
The surface and cross-sectional morphologies of the GQDs-PA/PVC NF membranes with different amounts of GQDs were shown in Fig. 9
                        . Interestingly, there was no noticeable structural change on the membrane surface over the experimental range of the GQD content studied. These three membranes (membrane M0.05-15, M0.1-15 and M0.5-15) had the PA layer thickness of 45 to 55 nm, which were consistent with the thickness of M0-15 membrane (Fig. 7 and 
                           Fig. S6

                        ). It may be noticed that different from the M0-40 membrane shown in Fig. 7, the M3-6 membrane, which was prepared with the longest electrospray time (40 min) and highest GQDs concentration (0.5 g/L) showed a clear layer-by-layer loose structure (see 
                           Fig. S8
                        ). This was caused by the large amount of GQDs embedded into the PA layer of M0.5-40 membrane under a long electrospray time.
